<p>I am trying to create a mysql cursor using the below command:-</p>  <p>Mysql command :-</p>  <pre><code>    DELIMITER $$     DECLARE a int;     DECLARE b varchar(255);     DECLARE SUN_CURSOR CURSOR FOR      SELECT address_id,post_code from address;     OPEN SUN_CURSOR;     FETCH SUN_CURSOR into a,b;     select a,b;     close SUN_CURSOR;     $$     DELIMITER ; </code></pre>  <p>When executing the above query i am getting the below error.can some one please help i tried to google but can't find anything useful.please help</p>  <p>Error:-</p>  <pre><code>#1064 - You have an error in your SQL syntax; check the manual that corresponds to your MySQL server version for the right syntax to use near 'DECLARE a int; DECLARE b varchar(255); DECLARE SUN_CURSOR CURSOR FOR  SELECT ' at line 1  </code></pre>  <p>Here Address is a table whose data i am trying to fetch using a cursor.</p>